result.execSummary:
This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Dentonicco Tywann Magett appeared by video.  Attorney Erica N Young appeared by video for Dentonicco Tywann Magett.  Prosecuting attorney Gregg Herman appeared by video for the State of Wisconsin. 
CASE HEARD OFF THE RECORD DUE TO COURT REPORTER AVAILABILITY.
Case in court for pretrial conference.
Defense counsel has not received discovery from the State. Defense counsel challenges probable cause in Criminal Complaint and requests motion hearing date.
Defense motion to be filed on or before 11/1/2022. State's response, if appropriate, to be filed on or before 11/21/2022.
Case remains calendared in Branch 15.
Motion hearing scheduled for December 2, 2022 at 03:00 pm.

Court orders defendant to report to the Milwaukee County Jail by 5:00 pm on 09-24-2022 to be booked and released. Failure to report will result in the issuance of a bench warrant. 

Defendant advised it is a requirement to attend all future court proceedings.
Failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping.

Defendant Dentonicco Tywann Magett in court. Student Intern Lukas Jaeger under the supervision of Attorney Sara Nicole Volden Sadowski in court for the State of Wisconsin. Deputy court clerk cmt. 
Defendant is advised that this case is assigned to Judge Watts, Branch 15.
Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause. Defendant received a copy of the complaint and was advised of right to counsel and maximum penalties. Court entered a plea of not guilty on behalf of the Defendant. Court reserves Defendant's right to file a substitution of judge pursuant to Sec. 971.20,right to challenge probable cause and to have complaint read until Defendant's next scheduled court appearance. Defendant IS Public Defender eligible. Defendant is ordered to provide the public defender's office with the next court date. The case is scheduled for a Pretrial Conference in Br 15.
Pre-trial conference scheduled for October 12, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Summons mailed.  Defendant ordered into room 221 Safety Building on 9/22/22 @ 1:30p
